Day 56 – Road to Fluent Spanish Summary

Today’s Spanish study session focused heavily on conversational fluency, recommendation phrases, practical travel communication, invitation structures, reflexive verbs, shopping/travel dialogue, and continued review of Pimsleur Unit 2 Lesson 12. Strong emphasis was placed on improving spontaneous recall speed and understanding more difficult conversational structures involving past tense, object pronouns, and reflexive phrasing.

Duolingo Review:
Reviewed several useful conversational and descriptive vocabulary words including:

el pasillo = hallway / aisle
la maestría = master’s degree
la cafetería = cafe
aficionado = fan / enthusiast
el bailarín = dancer
el proceso de admisión = admission process
fuera = outside
enamorada = in love
oficina = office
Memrise Review:
Focused on practical conversational and descriptive phrases:

tenemos que subir la producción de la empresa = we have to increase the company’s production
Julia no está enamorada = Julia is not in love
está en una oficina = it is in an office
está lleno de gente los sábados = it’s crowded on Saturdays
la cafetería del centro comercial es pequeña, pero no es ruidosa = the cafe at the mall is small, but not noisy
¿cuánto cuesta este libro? = how much does this book cost?
¿cuánto cuestan estos? = how much do these cost?
